cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.MM, cs.NE 

The paper proposes a framework for improving object and action localization in images and videos, which falls under the computer vision (cs.CV) and multimedia (cs.MM) categories. The approach is based on modifying the input image and training a network, which involves machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The paper also mentions using a network designed for object localization, which could potentially involve neural networks (cs.NE).
